# selid: # reg_class_name = Class name of the register
# reg_name = Instance name of the register
# res_type = The register is accessible only if the mechanithm is enabled. If disabled
# priv = Accessible privilege mode. If the register is accessed by lower mode
#        If register has different mode for each PE or R/W access type
#        set lowest mode and check the mode in Read/Write function for each register.
# id = If multiple registers is instantiated from same "reg_class_name" class
#      the id number will be put for them to distinguish for each.
# bankid = The bank id of MPU entry registers.
# base = name of base class for the register.

regid: virtualized registers have common base classes.
